wc commands means word count
It will number of characters, words, lines etc in a file


fokhrul@fokhrul-VirtualBox:~$ cd Desktop/
fokhrul@fokhrul-VirtualBox:~/Desktop$ ls
Bangladesh.txt  file.txt  folder2  script1.sh

fokhrul@fokhrul-VirtualBox:~/Desktop$ wc Bangladesh.txt       ;29 is the number of line
  29  458 2899 Bangladesh.txt                                 ;458 is the number of words
                                                              ;2899 is the number of characters
                                                              
fokhrul@fokhrul-VirtualBox:~/Desktop$ wc -c Bangladesh.txt    ;number of characters
2899 Bangladesh.txt

fokhrul@fokhrul-VirtualBox:~/Desktop$ wc -l Bangladesh.txt    ;number of lines
29 Bangladesh.txt

fokhrul@fokhrul-VirtualBox:~/Desktop$ wc -w Bangladesh.txt    ;number of words
458 Bangladesh.txt 

fokhrul@fokhrul-VirtualBox:~/Desktop$ wc -L Bangladesh.txt    ;number of characters in the longest line
292 Bangladesh.txt
